LLM 

1. Intro:

a. Deep NNs trained on LARGE amount of data.
b. ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude etc, all use LLMs (have their own LLMs —> NNs trained on HUGE data)
** 
c. WHY “LLM”? —> They deal with billions of parameters, even trillions. e.g -> GPT3 has 150+ Billion parameters. (In 1900s,  there used to be only 100-150 parameters)
**

d. Their token size is too big
e. LLMs only deal with Language. (NLP)
f. Small NLP models were designed for specific tasks. LLMs cover a wide range
g. WHAT MAKES LLM TOO GOOD?   —> Transformer architecture
h. AI —> ML —> DL —> LLM (Order)
I. GenAI --> LLM + DL

Applications of LLM:
-> chatbots/ virtual assistants
-> machine translation 
-> sentiment analysis etc
-> Context creation

